;起源
黑死病的源头无定论，但一般认为来自[[亚洲|亚洲]]<ref name=":1" /><ref name=":13" /><ref name=":8">{{Cite web|title=How the Black Death Started in Asia|url=https://www.thoughtco.com/black-death-in-asia-bubonic-plague-195144|author=Kallie Szczepanski|date=2019-08-12|last=|first=|work=|publisher=ThoughtCo|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210720021102/https://www.thoughtco.com/black-death-in-asia-bubonic-plague-195144|archive-date=2021-07-20|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=":11">{{Cite journal|title=Was the Black Death in India and China?|url=https://www.jstor.org/stable/44452010|last=SUSSMAN|first=GEORGE D.|date=2011|journal=Bulletin of the History of Medicine|issue=3|volume=85|pages=319–355|issn=0007-5140}}</ref>。有研究人员认为该病起源于[[中國|中国]]（[[蒙元|蒙元]]）或者邻近地区<ref name=":5" /><ref name=":9" /><ref name=":8" /><ref>{{Cite journal|title=Phylogenetic diversity and historical patterns of pandemic spread of Yersinia pestis|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2999892/|last=Morelli|first=Giovanna|last2=Song|first2=Yajun|date=2010-12|journal=Nature genetics|issue=12|doi=10.1038/ng.705|volume=42|pages=1140–1143|issn=1061-4036|pmc=2999892|pmid=21037571|last3=Mazzoni|first3=Camila J.|last4=Eppinger|first4=Mark|last5=Roumagnac|first5=Philippe|last6=Wagner|first6=David M.|last7=Feldkamp|first7=Mirjam|last8=Kusecek|first8=Barica|last9=Vogler|first9=Amy J.}}</ref><ref name=":6">{{Cite web|title=Black Death may have originated in China|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/asia/china/8102278/Black-Death-may-have-originated-in-China.html|date=2010-11-01|work=The Telegraph|language=en-GB|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210724205655/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/asia/china/8102278/Black-Death-may-have-originated-in-China.html|archive-date=2021-07-24|dead-url=no}}</ref>，譬如元帝國和[[察合台汗國|察合台汗國]]交接的[[天山山脉|天山山脉]]<ref name=":10">{{Cite journal|title=Death by the Lake: Mortality Crisis in Early Fourteenth-Century Central Asia|url=https://direct.mit.edu/jinh/article/50/1/59/49591/Death-by-the-Lake-Mortality-Crisis-in-Early|last=Slavin|first=Philip|date=2019-05-01|journal=The Journal of Interdisciplinary History|issue=1|doi=10.1162/jinh_a_01376|volume=50|pages=59–90|language=en|issn=0022-1953}}</ref>。1331–34年，[[大元帝國|大元帝國]]境内曾爆发流行病，[[河北省|河北]]等地受灾严重，有估计数百万人因此死亡<ref name=":8" /><ref name=":11" /><ref>{{Cite web|title=The Black Death: Timeline|url=http://hosted.lib.uiowa.edu/histmed/plague/plaguetimeline.html|work=|publisher=[[爱荷华大学|爱荷华大学]]|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210720015618/http://hosted.lib.uiowa.edu/histmed/plague/plaguetimeline.html|archive-date=2021-07-20|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=从黑死病到新冠：大流行如何终结？|url=https://cn.nytimes.com/health/20200512/coronavirus-plague-pandemic-history/|date=2020-05-12|last=Kolata|first=Gina|work=|publisher=《[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]》|language=zh|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210720021123/https://cn.nytimes.com/health/20200512/coronavirus-plague-pandemic-history/|archive-date=2021-07-20|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=瘟疫与人：欧洲鼠疫的大流行|url=https://www.thepaper.cn/newsDetail_forward_5598718|author=威廉·麦克尼尔|date=2020-01-28|authorlink=威廉·H·麦克尼尔|work=[[澎湃新闻|澎湃新闻]]|publisher=《瘟疫与人》（中信出版·见识城邦）|language=zh|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210716023733/https://www.thepaper.cn/newsDetail_forward_5598718|archive-date=2021-07-16|dead-url=no}}</ref>；1344年、1350年间也爆发过疫情<ref name=":11" />。该疾病可能由[[蒙古帝国|蒙古帝国]]军队和商队沿着[[丝绸之路|丝绸之路]]传播<ref name=":6" />。还有研究人员认为黑死病来自于[[中亚|中亚]]地区，譬如[[裡海|裡海]]<ref name=":4">{{Cite journal |last=Haensch |first=Stephanie |last2=Bianucci |first2=Raffaella |last3=Signoli |first3=Michel |last4=Rajerison |first4=Minoarisoa |last5=Schultz |first5=Michael |last6=Kacki |first6=Sacha |last7=Vermunt |first7=Marco |last8=Weston |first8=Darlene A. |last9=Hurst |first9=Derek |date=2010-10-07 |title=Distinct Clones of Yersinia pestis Caused the Black Death |url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2951374/ |journal=PLoS Pathogens |volume=6 |issue=10 |doi=10.1371/journal.ppat.1001134 |issn=1553-7366 |pmc=2951374 |pmid=20949072}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title=Modeling the epidemiological history of plague in Central Asia: Palaeoclimatic forcing on a disease system over the past millennium|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2944127/|last=Kausrud|first=Kyrre Linné|last2=Begon|first2=Mike|date=2010-08-27|journal=BMC Biology|doi=10.1186/1741-7007-8-112|volume=8|pages=112|issn=1741-7007|pmc=2944127|pmid=20799946|last3=Ari|first3=Tamara Ben|last4=Viljugrein|first4=Hildegunn|last5=Esper|first5=Jan|last6=Büntgen|first6=Ulf|last7=Leirs|first7=Herwig|last8=Junge|first8=Claudia|last9=Yang|first9=Bao}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|chapter=|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=tzRwRmb09rgC&pg=PA31#v=onepage&q&f=false|publisher=Infobase Publishing|date=2007|isbn=978-1-4381-2923-5|language=en|first=George C.|last=Kohn|title=Encyclopedia of Plague and Pestilence: From Ancient Times to the Present}}</ref>。此外，也有研究人员认为黑死病来自[[俄国|俄国]]的[[伏尔加河|伏尔加河]]流域<ref>{{Cite web|title=Ancient DNA traces the Black Death to Russia's Volga region|url=https://www.sciencemag.org/news/2019/10/ancient-dna-traces-black-death-russia-s-volga-region|date=2019-10-02|last=Gibbons|first=Ann|work=|publisher=Science|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210720015731/https://www.sciencemag.org/news/2019/10/ancient-dna-traces-black-death-russia-s-volga-region|archive-date=2021-07-20|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2022年6月，刊登於《[[自然_(期刊)|自然]]》的研究論文以考古發掘與科學分析推定黑死病源頭可能在今中亞國家[[吉爾吉斯|吉爾吉斯]]東北部，位於[[天山|天山]]山腳下的[[伊塞克湖|伊塞克湖]]附近<ref name=":13" />。該處在1338年至1339年間出現大量墓碑，死因為「mawtānā」（[[敘利亞語|敘利亞語]]的瘟疫），從墓地埋葬的牙齒遺骸進行DNA比對，其體內含有[[鼠疫桿菌|鼠疫桿菌]]，且該菌株是透過[[土撥鼠|土撥鼠]]傳染給人類<ref name=":13" />。[[貿易|貿易]]與戰爭可能是鼠疫傳到歐洲的決定性因素<ref name=":13" /><ref>[https://www.storm.mg/article/4382564 世紀瘟疫病源找到了！新研究發現歐洲中世紀「黑死病」最初來自「這個地方」]</ref>。

;傳播
1345–46年，蒙古[[金帐汗国|金帐汗国]]第十一任可汗[[札尼别|札尼别]]的军队在围攻[[克里米亚|克里米亚]][[卡法|卡法]]城期间，将军队中[[鼠疫|鼠疫]]病死者从城外抛到城内（也可能是受感染的老鼠进入城中传播），致使卡法城内的许多士兵和居民染上鼠疫<ref name=":1" /><ref name=":7">{{Cite journal|title=Biological Warfare at the 1346 Siege of Caffa - Volume 8, Number 9—September 2002 - Emerging Infectious Diseases journal - CDC|url=https://wwwnc.cdc.gov/eid/article/8/9/01-0536_article|last=Wheelis|first=Mark|doi=10.3201/eid0809.010536|language=en-us}}</ref>。城内的许多商人不得不弃城西逃，越过[[黑海|黑海]]到达[[君士坦丁堡|君士坦丁堡]]，使得黑死病于1347年夏进入欧洲<ref name=":1" /><ref name=":7" />。其中，[[拜占庭帝国皇帝|拜占庭帝国皇帝]][[约翰六世·坎塔库泽努斯|约翰六世·坎塔库泽努斯]]13岁的儿子也感染此病丧生<ref>{{Cite book|chapter=The Black Death and Its Aftermath (1347–1453)|title=Plague and Empire in the Early Modern Mediterranean World: The Ottoman Experience, 1347–1600|url=https://www.cambridge.org/core/books/plague-and-empire-in-the-early-modern-mediterranean-world/black-death-and-its-aftermath-13471453/15DB5DF086CF40DCC1C8CBB5078FD2B3|publisher=Cambridge University Press|date=2015|location=Cambridge|isbn=978-1-107-01338-4|pages=90–128|editor-first=Nükhet|editor-last=Varlik}}</ref>。此后，黑死病传播到[[意大利|意大利]]的[[西西里王國|西西里王國]]和[[威尼斯共和國|威尼斯共和國]]等地，并逐渐蔓延至[[法国|法国]]、西班牙諸國、[[葡萄牙王國|葡萄牙王國]]、[[英格兰王國|英格兰王國]]、[[神聖羅馬帝國|神聖羅馬帝國]]等欧洲各国<ref name=":1" /><ref name=":7" />。

===鳥嘴医生===
{{main|瘟疫醫生}}
“鳥嘴医生”是黑死病肆虐時期，歐洲各地專門醫治患者的醫師。他們會戴著具有防傳染功能的鳥喙狀[[面具|面具]]來治療病患，因此被稱為“鳥嘴医生”。這些瘟疫醫師往往沒受過多少醫學訓練，也缺乏臨床診斷能力；然而由於當時歐洲人手奇缺，因此這些醫生是各個城鎮相當珍貴的資產。

“鳥嘴醫生”身穿長袍，會使用一種木製的拐杖碰觸病人治病。也用於鞭打病人以赦免他們的罪，因為當時的人們相信罹患黑死病是不受上帝庇祐的惡人，而唯有透過鞭笞，病人才能從上天的懲罰中獲得救贖。<ref>Pommerville, p. 9</ref><ref>O'Donnell, p. 143</ref>

